  "text": "The preBö tzinger Complex (preBö tC) is a heterogeneous medullary population of $1,000-3,000 neurons/side that is the presumptive kernel for respiratory rhythm generation in rodents [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] and presumably in humans [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . preBö tC heterogeneity is reflected in various molecularly defined subpopulations that may underlie different functions during breathing [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] ).",
